{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "slack-mock-collection-2026",
    "name": "Slack Mock API – Training Collection",
    "description": "# Slack Mock API – Student Training Collection\n\nUse this collection to practice interacting with the Slack Mock Service running locally on port **4003**.\n\n## 🔑 Authentication — Required for every request\n\nEvery API request must include this header:\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer xoxb-mock-bot-token\n```\nThis is already configured via the **Slack Mock – Local** environment. Just select it and you're ready.\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n1. Import this collection **and** `Slack_Mock.postman_environment.json`\n2. Select the **Slack Mock – Local** environment (top-right dropdown in Postman)\n3. Make sure the Slack Mock server is running on `http://localhost:4003`\n4. Run **Health Check** first to verify the server is up\n5. Run **Send Message** to post to `#qa-reports` — the `ts` is auto-saved to `{{message_ts}}`\n6. Use that variable in Update Message, Delete Message, Add Reaction, etc.\n\n## 📚 Folder Structure\n- **System** — health check, auth test\n- **Conversations** — list channels, get channel info, create channel, get history, get members, get thread replies\n- **Chat** — send message, update message, delete message\n- **Users** — list users, get user info\n- **Reactions** — add reaction, get reactions\n- **Files** — upload a file\n\n## 🌱 Seed Data\n| Resource | Values |\n|---|---|\n| Channels | `qa-reports` (C1234567890), `general` (C0987654321), `dev-alerts` (C1122334455) |\n| Users | `alice` (U1111111111), `bob` (U2222222222), `charlie` (U3333333333) |\n| Token | `xoxb-mock-bot-token` (any `xoxb-*` or `xoxp-*` value works) |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{api_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "System",
      "description": "Health check and authentication verification",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Verify the Slack Mock server is running. No auth required."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"healthy\",\n  \"service\": \"slack-mock\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },

        {
          "name": "Auth Test",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Auth test ok', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.true);",
                  "pm.test('Returns team info', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().team).to.be.a('string'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth.test",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth.test"]
            },
            "description": "Validate your token and get workspace info. Equivalent to real Slack's `auth.test`.\n\n**Expected response:**\n```json\n{\"ok\": true, \"team\": \"Mock Workspace\", \"user\": \"mock_bot\", ...}\n```\n\n**If token is missing:** `{\"ok\": false, \"error\": \"not_authed\"}`\n**If token is wrong:** `{\"ok\": false, \"error\": \"invalid_auth\"}`"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK – valid token",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
              "body": "{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"url\": \"https://mockslack.slack.com/\",\n  \"team\": \"Mock Workspace\",\n  \"user\": \"mock_bot\",\n  \"team_id\": \"T0MOCKTEAM1\",\n  \"user_id\": \"USLACKBOT\",\n  \"bot_id\": \"B0MOCKBOT01\",\n  \"is_enterprise_install\": false\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "200 – invalid_auth",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
              "body": "{\n  \"ok\": false,\n  \"error\": \"invalid_auth\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "Conversations",
      "description": "Channel management — list, info, create, history, members, replies.\n\nAll requests use: `Authorization: Bearer {{api_token}}`",
      "item": [

